reviews: The Babel is a very nice boutique hotel. Modest sized room as normal for Paris, but a fairly large bathroom with a very nice shower. The hotel and rooms are all decorated with a "Tower of Babel" theme, and our room was very cute. The breakfast is a superior continental breakfast with bread, croissants, tea or coffee, and a choice from a few add-ons like yogurt with granola. The hotel restaurant is pretty good, and we had a nice meal there. All the staff are very helpful and friendly. Any reasonable request is quickly fulfilled. Located in a slightly off beat part of Paris, but only a few minutes walk from a metro station. Many bustling streets nearby.

We had an incredible stay at Babel. Staff were professional and always willing to help/ accommodate our needs. The restaurant is top notch and was popular with guests and locals alike. Our rooms were snug yet smartly accessorized with great attention to detail. We enjoyed the variety of cultures and experiences in the Belleville neighborhood; the proximity to landmarks without being in the middle of tourist traps was perfect for us. I would highly recommend this hotel.

Really nice hotel, great location, lovely breakfast. Staff were generally very friendly.

My only negative is that I had specifically pre-warned of some dietary requirements to allow plenty of time for preparation but these werenâ€™t fully met and when I asked for some suitable milk I was made to feel like I was a huge inconvenience by the lady serving breakfast. I also had no bread on the second day which meant that although I paid the same price as everyone else I was only able to have half of the breakfast.

Really well designed hotel. The bar and bedrooms are beautifully curated with a lovely ambience. The staff were all really welcoming and friendly. Music and in house scents were perfect.
Bedroom was compact but with comfortable bed, quality furnishings, good shower and blackout curtains/decent soundproofing. We slept well here.
The breakfast was efficiently served in a nice airy room. Croissant/bread, choice of yogurt, compote or chia with fruit and granola. Unlimited coffee and teas.
Perfect location for us, on a pedestrian street two minutes from the Belleville metro. Easy access to the rest of Paris on foot or public transport.
Really vibrant area with loads of bars and quality dining opportunities. Street art everywhere. It felt safe. Brilliant place to stay if you want a more quirky and non touristy neighbourhood.
Huge, friendly veg/fruit market on Tuesdays and Fridays.
Our new fave base in Paris!

We loved our stay so much the first half of our trip so much we rebooked for one night before our outbound flight from Paris. The rooms are cozy but clean and very stylish. Great value for your money. The breakfast was excellent and is served in a light-filled restaurant space. The hotel is situated in a gentrifying working class neighborhood and near bakeries, LP bars and Vietnamese restaurants where you can pick up an amazing banh mi sandwich. Also, the 2 and 11 metro lines are 5 minutes away. But most of all we will remember the consistent warmth and helpfulness of the staff at Babel Belleville who answered all our questions and treated us like visiting family.

Stayed for two nights. Nice room, very clean and quiet. Friendly staff, breakfast was good and food very fresh. The location also good, a little bit on the side in a busy area with lots of art, creative athosphere and a mixture of people.

Elegant and comfortable. The decor is tasteful and thoughtful, with every detail considered. The staff is friendly and accommodating. The food is terrific: breakfasts delicious infilling, and dinner was exciting;. Our new favorite Pais hotel.

Room has very comfortable bed. linen, pillows, blanket, matress. All of these has a high quality and help me slept reaÃ¶Ã¶y well during my visit.
Hotel room bathroom was really clean and had a separated spacious showeroom.

Pros:

- location could not be better
- connected to two major stations that take you easily to anywhere in the city
- a chance to stay in a "real" Parisian neighbourhood where tourists don't outnumber the local Parisians
- good bed
- good water pressure and hot showers
- quiet

Cons
- sink was too small. Needed to wash face in the shower to avoid splashing water everywhere
- small bugs in the room that stung (see photo). I am not sure what they were. They were mostly on the ceiling and seemed to be particularly active at night.

Other
- the showers are only appropriate for those who are okay being seen naked by their room-mate. The door to the shower is completely transparent and there is no other door between the shower and the bedroom

This 3 star hotel in Babelville is well located and only 2 minutes away from a metro-station.
The rooms are small but very clean. The beds have new mattresses. The design is a mixture between Morocco style and antiques. You will find a possibility to cook coffee or tea but will possibly miss a refrigerator.
The complementary breakfast is nice and lets you start the daywith fresh juice and Quinoa pudding.
We will definitely return.

We received a warm welcome for our week at Babel in a twin room. There is a great, busy vibe around the restaurant downstairs (you will need to book for dinner, although it is not open Sunday or Monday evening). Our room was beautifully appointed, air conditioned and very quietâ€¦ I wanted to take it with us on the rest of our holiday! The room was super clean and was serviced daily by friendly staff. The bathroom basin was in the room, but toilet was behind its own door, as was the generously sized shower. The bedding was very comfortable. Our window opened onto the Rue Lemon lane way. There are stairs and a fabulously decorated elevator if you are on a higher floor. There are plenty of services nearby. The Belleville metro entrance was about 50 meters away, food venues and laundromat very close by. Staff always on had if you need anything.

Yes, the room was small; this is a small french hotel in the 3 star category in one of the most expensive cities in the world. But everything was well appointed and the hand-painted walls were lovely. The elevator alone is worth a visit. Everyone was very friendly, speaking English or French as you like. Lovely breakfast and decent coffee. I would return to this hotel

I booked to stay in this hotel In July. Unfortunately due to some unforeseen personal issues I had to travel back to Australia and could not keep my reservation. I notified the hotel and asked that they keep my booking as a credit for when I returned in September. They agreed however when I went to rebook they then denied this and said I could not use my credit.

Unfortunately this lack of hospitality and understanding means I would never consider staying here again especially when there are so many amazing hotels in Paris - most of whom would understand that people need flexibility with their travel arrangements

This hotel is amazing. The decor is fantastic, middle Eastern vibe meets Parisian chic. There is nothing about this place that I can fault. The staff were wonderfully friendly and although we only ate breakfast here it was very good. Great quality ingredients and plentiful. The divine smell that came from the kitchen during the day would also suggest the main meals would most certainly be worth a try!

Can't thank you all enough for making our short stay here a very memorable one. Will definitely be back.

Lucy

Beautiful hotel with great design and attention to details. The staff is warm and attentive. The rooms are small and very cozy, good to share only if you are VERY comfortable with your travel companion.
The restaurant is great, with an inventive, beautifully crafted cocktail program that is worth a visit on its own! Very quick and easy to get around Paris by metro from the stop at the end of the block. Would stay again!

Although the hotel is pricey, this is not surprising in Paris. The rooms are small, also not a surprise in Paris, but the unique decoration and atmosphere more than make up for these minor issues. There is also no bathroom proper, but rather a shower and a sink basically in the room. I stayed there twice first at the end of May and then in early June and really liked my 2nd room because it was a bit bigger which allowed for the shower and sink to be a bit to the side.

I had dinner there with a friend and cannot recommend the food enough! It was delicious as well as unusual. We recommend the green pea "hummus".

Lastly, my first night I arrived super late as my luggage was missing at CDG and it took forever to figure that out, and when I arrived the receptionist and bartender made me feel so welcome! The staff is awesome.

I am definitely staying there on my next trip to Paris. Love the location as well!

We recently stayed in this hotel at the end of June at a very costly price for a family of 4, the location is handy for the metro but thatâ€™s about it !
The rooms are small and if you are travelling with a companion where shower and washing privately are important then these rooms will not suit as the shower and sink are in the bedroom !
The beds are comfortable and the hotel was quiet at night and no doors banging or noisy residents.
However the previous reviews about breakfast are true and should be considered if you are a tourist heading out for the day and need something substantial, it was so disappointing. The cost for 4 people for breakfast for 4 days was 160 euro for which we were given a glass of freshly squeezed orange juice, a small bowl of granola which none of us liked, one croissant and one slice of bread, a cup of coffee and we had to supply our own t bags. On our last day there werenâ€™t any croissants so we just left !
I did raise this with the hotel and after several emails they have offered a voucher for 160 euro knowing that the likelihood of us ever using this is minimal ,the absolute least they could have done was offer a refund for the day we had nothing.
**** to anyone reading this due to stay here soon we have asked them to extend the voucher to the next family that is staying there so hoping they will fulfill this request !

Wish I could have stayed two nights! Great vibe, great staff, and my room blissfully quiet (201, no street noise whatsoever), air conditioner did its job. Liked secure elevator, too, operated by guest card. Had dinner at restaurant and enjoyed the food and vibe, Carla in particular a rockstar front of house lady. Enjoyed exploring the neighborhood too.

I chose Babel Belleville because I wanted to stay off the beaten path, away from touristy areas. As I was visiting Paris on business and it was my second time visiting the city, thus I wanted to stay in a more local neighborhood.

Babel Belleville did not disappoint! Iâ€™m very happy with the price, service, restaurant and bar, my hotel room, and the location. The metro 2 and 11 lines are right outside around the corner, and there are fantastic authentic traditional French restaurants (as well as Chinese and other ethnic cuisines) nearby.

Their restaurant serves Lebanese dishes and unique cocktails. I had dinner once there and drinks a few of nights of my stay. I highly recommend dining here, even if youâ€™re not staying at Babel.

The hotel room itself is cozy and lovely. It is quite small, but perfect for a solo traveller like me. I really enjoyed the rain shower and natural eco soap/wash that was provided in the hotel room. I love the little details like the old fashioned phone and pieces of relics on the walls.

I would for sure stay here again!

Just had a three-night stay here and it was so lovely! I'd left it a little late to book a hotel so took a punt on this one as the reviews looked good. It's well located just off the Metro and tucked up a side street with a little restaurant below. Plenty of bars/restaurants within walking distance.

We only had a basic room, and it was certainly small, but there is an efficient use of space. The room was lovely and clean and had a good-sized bed for such a compact room.

The loveliest part of our stay was the staff. Incredibly friendly, helpful and extremely tolerant at my lack of French!

Very near the metro, convenient for the Gard Du Nord, this is a gem of a hotel. Rooms (at least some of them) are not big, but its quiet, beds are very comfy and the shower is fantastic. The rooms are great to stay in - have not slept that well in ages. No noise from the lively bar which turns into a great place for breakfast in the morning. Will become my essential stop in Paris (but it gets VERY booked up). The rooms we stayed in (bigger ones available) definitely better for singles with relatively little luggage as floor space not extensive.

We had a lovely meal here one evening and drinks in the buzzy bar on another night. The food is middle eastern and you pick 2-3 small plates each and share. There was no English menu, but the lady was very helpful with the translations!
We enjoyed the food which was all very fresh and yummy. For larger groups, there are some bigger sharing plates which are ideal for 3-4 people
On another evening, we came for drinks in the bar and enjoyed a couple of glasses of wine in a very convivial atmosphere

So glad I found this hotel. Exactly what I was looking for, something off-the-beaten-path. Great bedding (never slept better in a hotel), extremely quiet, fantastic breakfast (the homemade chia seed pudding is a delight, croissant super-flaky) and friendly staff. My only regret is that I didn't get to try their amazing dinner menu (yes, there is a restaurant too) because I had previously booked other venues. Can't wait to go back!

From the welcoming of the night receptionnist to the quality of the room and the bed, this place is perfect to stay in Paris and especially in Belleville.
All the team is warmfull and the breakfast is delicious ; simple and different from a classic buffet.
I recommend without any doubt

We spent 4 days at Babel Belleville with our 2 teen-agers and we loved everything ! Location, lovely guests, delicious breakfast and super cosy rooms .
We absolutely recommand it and will surely come back !

Hotel recently opened, you can see that. Room is so fresh and clean, tastefully decorated, we love the lightning.
The restaurant has some good cocktails and food on the menu (the hummus, yumm). Nearby public transport (metro Belleville) and in a pedestrian street. We'll sure stay in this hotel the next time that we are in Paris.

What a great experience it was to stay here. Super kind, helpful and friendly staff.
We went out for dinner but decided to go back and eat at the hotel. That was one of our best decisions this year! The food, dessert and cocktails were fantastic and the ambiance even more.

Itâ€™s all about the small details at Babel and I really appreciate that.

Too bad we had to leave but we will definitely be back.

Very welcoming, attentive staff. Overall magnificent experciende in hotel Babel, that is well located in multicultural neighbourhood. Only a few metrostops away from touristic highlights. Surprising discovery of dishes and flavors in the hotel restaurant.
Clean rooms, excellent bed and shower.

Absolutely fell in love with this hotel. Amazing vibe, great attention to details & interior design, comfy beds, delicious food, personable & helpful staff, and a super nice area of Paris - hip Belleville, calm quaint pedestrian street, with a few organic tapas-like restaurants close by). I stayed there for work & ended bringing my entire team there for cocktails. Will definitely be back - thanks Babel team for making my stay in Paris so delightful and energising!

We had an amazing weekend at the hotel! The hotel is brand new, the decoration is very cool and the food is amazing! I absolutely recommend the restaurant and the Sunday brunch! We had an amazing moment, weâ€™ll return for sure!
